    "long_description": "WelcomHeritage Mandir Palace is an architectural marvel of intricate stone carving, located just outside the Jaisalmer Fort. Built over two centuries, with the main portion constructed by Maharawal Jawahir Singh ji, it is the present residence of the Maharawal of Jaisalmer.\n\nThe palace showcases the exquisite craftsmanship of local stone carvers with its ornate balconies, canopies, and screens. It offers a unique opportunity to stay in a living palace that is still central to the royal family's life. The museum within the palace displays a collection of royal artifacts, adding to the immersive heritage experience.",
